column5: I was thinking of going fishing friday for pike on lake dalyrmpal but I was wondering if anyone has any info on the water condition and if the ice is gone?  Thnaks,  Matt
I was wondering the same thing Lot's of pike in there and Crappie. I was thinking of going Friday also are you launching in the narrows?
Yeah I was because the camp grounds arent open yet. I just hope that the water levels aren't to low over there.
when is the season open? I always thought pike closed for April
Yea usually it is but lake dalyrmpal is in zone 17 and the yhave pike open all year around.
i was up there on monday for a drive... still lots of ice on the lake... the narrows are ice free though... hope that helps.

Thnaks gone_fishin, Its good to know that the narrows are ice free. I still might give it a shot on friday and hopefully the warm weather this week opened up the lake abit more to get a bit of fishing in
Thanks gone_ fishin. If your up that way again please let me know of the ice conditions. It's a 2 hour drive for me. You could save me a trip.
I'll see you guys out there. I was hoping to hit up canal and Dalrympal the next two days
Was talking to my folks (who live on the lake) and they said the ice is gone...

I was also thinking of doing some fishing there on Saturday, I have two friends that live right on the lake and they both told me the ice is completely gone. Not too sure about the water levels though. Maybe I will see you up there.
hmm just got home from canal lake.. no pike to show off.. water levels were VERY LOW and im sure dalrympal is the same :|

well got back from Dalrymple yesterday.. not to upset.. saw a few pike.. but didnt Land any :| also saw two tiger musky.. that was pretty cool.. as i have never seen one before. ontop of that I saw ALOT of walleye up shallow while i was hunting for Pike.. all in all not a bad day.. plenty of people out there enjoying the new regs.. and all in all just havining a good time

Was also out yesterday didnt manage to catch any pike i think the water temp was still abit to cold for them to bit, but it was still a great day to be out on the water, i wish I wore sunscreen though im feeling the burn today lol. What size were the tiger muskie?
haha ya sun burn would of been nice the past two days.. to bad im stuburn.. as for the tiger musky I'll say about 30"
looks like i might be planning a camping trip this summer with my son ! where are the camp sites? pike, muskie & walleye how is the fishing there? cause it sucks in chemong.
The one i usually go to is called lazee acres.  The fishing there is pretty good for the most part, even though last year it wasnt the greatest.
